result.execSummary:
All charges against Shunga Orlinda Wright in this case have been dismissed. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Shunga Orlinda Wright is presumed innocent.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.
result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Shunga Orlinda Wright

records.addlTxt: Extradition was dismissed by motion of the State.

9:07 AM; Case called for Hearing. Prosecuting attorney Kristi J Gordon in court for the State of Wisconsin.   Defendant Shunga Orlinda Wright in court.  Attorney Luis Daniel Gutierrez in court for Shunga Orlinda Wright.  Court notes the matter is before the Court regarding the status of the State obtaining a Governor's warrant and inquires as to the status.  Atty. Gordon advises the State has not been able to obtain a Governor's Warrant and moves to have the case dismissed.  No objection by Atty. Gutierrez; he just requests the cash bail that was posted be refunded to the poster.  Court will grant the State's motion to dismiss and will order that the cash bail on deposit be refunded to the poster.

11:22 AM; Case called for Hearing. Prosecuting attorney Andrew Nesheim in court for the State of Wisconsin.   Defendant Shunga Orlinda Wright in court.  Attorney Luis Daniel Gutierrez in court for Shunga Orlinda Wright.  Court notes the matter was set for status with respect to the State obtaining the Governor's Warrant for extension of time.  Atty. Nesheim advises that his office as no word with respect to the Governor's Warrant and do not have a signed Warrant at this time.  Atty. Gutierrez moves to have the matter dismissed and presents arguments.  Atty. Nesheim notes the State has 60 days from 07/06/2022 so there are about 7 days left to try to obtain the Governor's Warrant.  Atty. Gutierrez confirms that information.  Court will adjourn for another status shortly after September 6.  Court advises the State that if they are not able to obtain the Governor's Warrant by 9/6/2022 they can advise the court in writing and the matter can be removed from the calendar.
Hearing scheduled for September 7, 2022 at 09:00 am.
Effective August 1, 2022, this case is assigned to Branch 7 Judicial Vacancy, pursuant to 22-SO-04(67).

09:29 AM; Case called for Hearing.  Defendant Shunga Orlinda Wright in court with attorney Luis Daniel Gutierrez.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern Nikole Kane appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court notes this is a follow-up from last week and inquires what the status of the case is.  State advises they are seeking a 60 day extension to obtain the Governor's Warrant.  Atty. Gutierrez advises he has no objection to the State's request for 60 day extension and also notes that he was incorrect at the last hearing in stating the court should sign the Warrant for Commitment and as his client has posted bail he is asking the court to not sign the Warrant for Commitment.  Court will grant the State's request for a 60 day extension from 07/06/2022.  Court will adjourn for another status to make sure the Governor's Warrant has been received the State.  Hearing scheduled for August 29, 2022 at 11:00 am.

09:00 AM; Case called for Hearing.  Defendant Shunga Orlinda Wright in court with attorney Luis Daniel Gutierrez.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern Julian Marrufo appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court notes the defendant is contesting extradition.  Atty. Gutierrez presents statements; he believes the Court still needs to sign the Warrant for Commitment and from there the 30 days should begin for the Governor's Warrant to come in.  State is asking the matter be set over for review in 30 days to allow time for them to receive the Governor's Warrant.  Court will adjourn for continued status to next week to allow time for the State to receive the Governor's Warrant.  Hearing scheduled for July 18, 2022 at 09:00 am.

Prior: 1420 S 54th St, West Milwaukee, WI 53214
Defendant to comply with I.D. Processing.

02:26 PM Defendant Shunga Orlinda Wright in court, in custody, with attorney Luis Daniel Gutierrez.    District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant is eligible for State Public Defender representation.  An attorney will be appointed.  Defense acknowledges receipt of complaint and accompanying affidavit and waives reading of complaint and affidavit.  Service admitted/advised of charges and potential penalties.  Attorney Gutierrez states the defendant wishes to contest the extradition.  The Court sets cash bail of $10,000.00.  The Court will set this matter for a status date before the trial court next week to address further scheduling.  Hearing scheduled for July 11, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Affidavit and out of state warrant
